The vivacious <b>Ruth Woodall</b> was selected as Miss Miami, and represented Florida in the 1925 Miss America Pageant in Atlantic City, New Jersey, where she was a semi-finalist.

She is seen here shaking hands with <b>Armand T. Nichols</b>, Director General of the Miss America Pageant. [<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miss_America_1925" rel="nofollow">1</a>] [<a href="http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2206&amp;dat=19250914&amp;id=XzIuAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=G9cFAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=5091,3447753" rel="nofollow">2</a>]
